[1] USA (Indiana)
Date: Sat 24 Feb 2018
Source: Washington Times Herald [edited]
http://www.washtimesherald.com/news/local_news/whooping-cough-on-the-rise-in-daviess-county/article_dd4eec36-4695-5ad7-bf87-bab9146c0061.html


The amount of whooping cough cases in Daviess County has already doubled from last year's numbers [2017]. "We usually only have one to 2 cases a year," Daviess County public health nurse Kathy Sullender said. "This year [2018] we have already had 4 cases. Three of the 4 cases had not received a vaccination," Sullender said. "The one that was vaccinated had a very mild case."

For questions about any vaccine or to schedule shots, call the Daviess County Health Department at 812-254-8666.

[byline: Kristi Sanders]

