[2] USA (Ohio)
Date: Tue 27 Feb 2018
Source: Examiner [edited]
http://www.examiner.org/news/93519-local-whooping-cough-cases-reported-vaccine-encouraged


Officials from the Logan County Health District reported [Tue 27 Feb 2018] that cases of pertussis, also known as whooping cough, are on the rise in the community, with 4 local cases confirmed, and the Tdap and DTap vaccines are encouraged for area residents.

These vaccines are available at the health district, 310 S Main St, during regular immunization clinic hours, from 9 to 11 am. Thursdays and from 2 to 6 pm the 1st Thursday of each month. Call 651-6186 to register.

To learn more about whooping cough and the vaccines to prevent it, visit <www.cdc.gov/whoopingcough> or talk to your health care professional.

