[3] USA (Idaho)
Date: Sat 3 Mar 2018
Source: WENY [edited]
http://www.weny.com/story/37626183/health-department-treasure-valley-whooping-cough-cases-on-the-rise


Reports of pertussis (also known as whooping cough) are on the rise in Ada and Canyon counties. Over the past 4 months, 89 cases have been reported -- 70 of those cases include Ada County residents, while 19 are Canyon County residents.

Whooping cough cases tend to peak every 3 to 5 years. The last peak was in 2014-2015, when nearly 300 cases of whooping cough were reported in Ada and Canyon counties. "The latest cycle of whooping cough began hitting Ada County back in October of last year [2017], while Canyon County cases began increasing in January of this year [2018]," Myron said [Christine Myron with the Central District Health Department in Boise].

[byline: Steve Bertel]

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Ada County, with a population of 392 365 residents in 2010, is located in the south western part of the US state of Idaho; its county seat and largest city is Boise, the state capital (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ada_County,_Idaho). The adjacent Canyon County, with a population of 188 923 residents in 2010, is part of the Boise Metropolitan Statistical Area in the US state of Idaho (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canyon_County,_Idaho#Adjacent_counties). A map of Idaho counties can be found at https://geology.com/county-map/idaho.shtml. - Mod.ML]

